You'll need two colors--white and green. The white frosting will be slathered on top of the cupcake, whereas the green frosting will be piped over the sugar cone. Spoon green frosting into the piping bag and add a small tip. If you don't have a piping bag at home, no worries--use a large, re-sealable plastic bag instead. Spoon frosting into the bag and then smooth out air pockets before sealing. Snip a small hole on one corner and twist bag until you've created a piping bag. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/82/Create-Christmas-Tree-Cupcakes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Create-Christmas-Tree-Cupcakes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/82/Create-Christmas-Tree-Cupcakes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Create-Christmas-Tree-Cupcakes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
